ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v281.message

Class VXU_V04

  • java.lang.Object
    • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractStructure
      • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractGroup
        • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.AbstractMessage
          • ca.uhn.hl7v2.model.v281.message.VXU_V04
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Group, Message, Structure, Visitable, Serializable

    public class VXU_V04
extends AbstractMessage

    Represents a VXU_V04 message structure (see chapter 4.A.6). This structure contains the following elements:

    • 1: MSH (Message Header)
    • 2: SFT (Software Segment) optional repeating
    • 3: UAC (User Authentication Credential Segment) optional
    • 4: PID (Patient Identification)
    • 5: PD1 (Patient Additional Demographic) optional
    • 6: NK1 (Next of Kin / Associated Parties) optional repeating
    • 7: ARV (Access Restriction) optional repeating
    • 8: VXU_V04_PATIENT_VISIT (a Group object) optional
    • 9: GT1 (Guarantor) optional repeating
    • 10: VXU_V04_INSURANCE (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 11: VXU_V04_PERSON_OBSERVATION (a Group object) optional repeating
    • 12: VXU_V04_ORDER (a Group object) optional repeating
    See Also:
    Serialized Form
